## API

- [Overview](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dotnet/docs/refs/heads/llmstxt/docs/machine-learning/tutorials/index.md): Explore the ML.NET tutorials to learn how to build custom AI solutions and integrate them into your .NET applications.
- [Analyze sentiment (binary classification)](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dotnet/docs/refs/heads/llmstxt/docs/machine-learning/tutorials/sentiment-analysis.md): This tutorial shows you how to create a .NET console application that classifies sentiment from website comments and takes the appropriate action. The binary sentiment classifier uses C# in Visual Studio.
- [Categorize support issues (multiclass classification)](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dotnet/docs/refs/heads/llmstxt/docs/machine-learning/tutorials/github-issue-classification.md): Discover how to use ML.NET in a multiclass classification scenario to classify GitHub issues to assign them to a given area.
- [Predict prices (regression)](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dotnet/docs/refs/heads/llmstxt/docs/machine-learning/tutorials/predict-prices.md): This tutorial illustrates how to build a regression model using ML.NET to predict prices, specifically, New York City taxi fares.
- [Categorize iris flowers (k-means clustering)](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dotnet/docs/refs/heads/llmstxt/docs/machine-learning/tutorials/iris-clustering.md): Learn how to use ML.NET in a clustering scenario
- [Recommend movies (matrix factorization)](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dotnet/docs/refs/heads/llmstxt/docs/machine-learning/tutorials/movie-recommendation.md): This tutorial shows you how to build a movie recommender with ML.NET in a .NET console application. The steps use C# and Visual Studio 2019.
- [Image classification (transfer learning)](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dotnet/docs/refs/heads/llmstxt/docs/machine-learning/tutorials/image-classification-api-transfer-learning.md): This tutorial illustrates how to use transfer learning to train a TensorFlow deep learning model in ML.NET using the image detection API to classify images of concrete surfaces as cracked or not cracked.
- [Classify images (model composition)](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dotnet/docs/refs/heads/llmstxt/docs/machine-learning/tutorials/image-classification.md): Learn how to train a classification model to categorize images using a pretrained TensorFlow model for image processing.
- [Forecast bike rental demand (time series)](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dotnet/docs/refs/heads/llmstxt/docs/machine-learning/tutorials/time-series-demand-forecasting.md): This tutorial shows you how to forecast demand for a bike rental service using univariate time-series analysis and ML.NET.
- [Call-volume spikes (anomaly detection)](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dotnet/docs/refs/heads/llmstxt/docs/machine-learning/tutorials/phone-calls-anomaly-detection.md): Learn how to build an anomaly detection application for time series data. This tutorial creates a .NET console application using C# in Visual Studio 2019.
- [Product sales analysis (anomaly detection)](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dotnet/docs/refs/heads/llmstxt/docs/machine-learning/tutorials/sales-anomaly-detection.md): Learn how to build an anomaly detection application for product sales data. This tutorial creates a .NET console application using C# in Visual Studio 2019.
- [Detect objects in images (object detection)](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dotnet/docs/refs/heads/llmstxt/docs/machine-learning/tutorials/object-detection-onnx.md): This tutorial illustrates how to use a pretrained ONNX deep learning model in ML.NET to detect objects in images.
- [Detect objects in images from Custom Vision ONNX model](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dotnet/docs/refs/heads/llmstxt/docs/machine-learning/tutorials/object-detection-custom-vision-onnx.md): Learn how to detect objects in images using an ONNX model from the Custom Vision service in ML.NET.
- [Classify sentiment using TensorFlow (text classification)](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dotnet/docs/refs/heads/llmstxt/docs/machine-learning/tutorials/text-classification-tf.md): This tutorial shows you how to use a pretrained TensorFlow model to classify sentiment in website comments. The binary sentiment classifier is a C# console application developed using Visual Studio.
